  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/savvy/e3c243e2-a35c-4786-95ee-f3ffb3b63e14/application",
    "company": "Savvy Wealth",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "d449a3d1c08e15ae",
    "department": "R\u0026D",
    "description": "ABOUT SAVVY WEALTH:\n\nWealth management is a $545 billion industry in the US, yet remains archaic and inefficient with low technology penetration. 75% of financial advisors don’t offer digital communication beyond email, and 62% still build financial plans manually in Excel. This leads to a poor client experience and results in financial advisors spending over 70% of their time on non-client facing, manual work.\n\nSavvy is changing that. We’re building the most advisor-centric platform in wealth management: a digital-first solution that modernizes human financial advice. Advisors who partner with Savvy tap into AI-powered software, automated sales and marketing, and seamless back office workflows to scale faster and spend more time with clients.\n\nWe’ve raised over $105M to date from Thrive Capital, Index Ventures, Canvas Ventures, Mark Casady (former LPL Financial CEO), and other top-tier investors. Our team is made up of repeat founders and operators who’ve helped build Airbnb, Square, Brex, Carta, Facebook, $200B+ RIAs, and more.\n\nSavvy is at a pivotal point in its growth trajectory, having established strong product-market fit in providing a modern platform to financial advisors. We’ve surpassed $5.1 billion in AUM in less than three years, grown 600%+ in the last 18 months, and are entering the next phase of the company which involves rapid expansion of our product offering and continued revenue growth. Come help us scale!\n\nThe Role:\n\nAs a Senior Product Designer at Savvy you'll take on one of the most complex and rewarding challenges in fintech: reimagining financial infrastructure, evolving our system of record, and innovating on an ideal advisor-powered client experience. You'll own the workflows where our platform meets legacy financial systems, and it will be your responsibility to challenge assumptions. This role is for a designer who thrives at the intersection of systems thinking, user empathy, and service design.\n\nThis is a high-ownership, high-impact role. You will lead complex initiatives end-to-end, from discovery through execution, while collaborating closely with product, engineering, operations, and advisors.\n\nThe ideal candidate is a systems thinker who thrives in ambiguity, understands complex service environments, and is excited to push the craft forward, especially by integrating AI into their design workflows.\n\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nDesign complex end-to-end experiences\n\n - Partner with Product Management and own major initiatives from research and discovery through high-fidelity execution and launch\n\n - Design across multiple user types (advisors, clients, operations) and ensure solutions account for downstream workflows and service realities.\n\n - Optimize for the service, not just the surface — designing with operational clarity, advisor workflows, and client communication in mind.\n\n - Identify opportunities where AI can meaningfully enhance the product experience.\n\nBring human signals into the product\n\n - Design high-trust experiences for sensitive financial moments such as onboarding, account transfers, and money movement.\n\n - Prioritize advisor presence, personalization, and clarity during moments of uncertainty or risk.\n\nApply and evolve design patterns thoughtfully\n\n - Leverage Savvy’s design system and established interaction patterns to create cohesive experiences.\n\n - Extend or adapt patterns when complex workflows or AI-driven features require clearer or more innovative solutions.\n\n - Actively incorporate AI tools into your workflow to accelerate exploration, prototyping, research synthesis, and iteration.\n\nResearch and discovery\n\n - Conduct user research with financial advisors and internal stakeholders using appropriate methods (i.e user interviews, surveys, card sorting, etc).\n\n - Translate research insights into clear product recommendations and design decisions.\n\n - Partner with product and engineering to define scope and priorities.\n\nEmbrace and evolve our culture\n\n - Contribute to a culture of thoughtful critique, high standards, and low ego collaboration.\n\n - Share learnings, tools, and AI-driven workflows that elevate the broader design and product team.\n\n - Provide constructive feedback to peers and cross-functional partners, helping maintain a strong culture of ownership and accountability.\n\n - Model curiosity, adaptability, and resilience in a fast-paced, evolving environment.\n\nMust Have:\n\n - You have 5-7 years of experience in product design, preferably in a fast-paced startup environment.\n\n - You’re excited about integrating AI tools into your design workflow and building AI-powered product experiences\n\n - You have experience designing complex systems or service-oriented products with multiple user types\n\n - You are an owner, have excellent problem-solving skills, and can prioritize tasks effectively with strong attention to detail.\n\n - You pride yourself in strong interaction design, systems thinking, and information architecture skills\n\n - You're a skilled communicator with the ability to absorb and distill complexity and drive decision-making.\n\n - You love backing your work with research, knowing that research pays dividends in translating insights into product decisions\n\n - You thrive in fast-paced, ambiguous environments and are a naturally curious, proactive self-starter who is constantly on the lookout for new opportunities and solutions.\n\n - You are a team player who’s excited to shape the future of wealth management\n\nNice to Have:\n\n - Experience designing in fintech, wealth management, or other high-trust, high-stakes domains\n\n\nBENEFITS:\n\n - Competitive salary and equity package\n\n - Unlimited PTO + paid company holidays\n\n - Access to holistic medical, dental, and vision plans\n\n - Company 401(k), Commuter, and HSA/FSA plans\n\n - NYC office in the heart of Manhattan\n\n - Lunch and snacks provided in the office\n\n - Access to virtual mental health care (Spring Health), vision related benefits (XP Health), and health concierge (Rightway) to help you find the right care\n\n - Access to counseling for stress management, dependent care, nutrition, fitness, legal, and financial issues (Guardian WorkLifeMatters EAP)",
